Implementation Plan - SOP & Work Order Integration
This plan details the steps to integrate Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs) directly into the Work Order workflow for engineers.

Proposed Changes
[Work Order Module]
[MODIFY] 
WorkOrderDetailsModal.tsx
New State: Add showSOPChecklist and selectedSOP states.
SOP Lookup: When the modal opens, if an asset is linked, search the local SOPs for a matching asset_type.
"Execute SOP Checklist" Button:
Add a button in the Asset detail row of the View Mode.
Visibility: Only show when workOrder.status === 'in_progress'.
Styling: Use a distinct maintenance color (emerald or blue) with a ClipboardCheck icon.
SOP Modal Integration:
Render the 
SOPModal
 as a child component.
Configure it for isEngineer (checklist) mode.
Pass the current workOrder.id to the 
SOPModal
 props.
User Flow
Engineer opens an Assigned Work Order.
Engineer clicks "Start Work".
Once the status is "In Progress", the "Execute SOP Checklist" button becomes active.
Engineer clicks the button to open the procedure.
Engineer ticks off steps as they work.
Engineer clicks "Submit Execution" to save the record permanently.
Engineer records final diesel/meter readings and closes the Work Order.
Verification Plan
Automated Tests
N/A (Manual Verification in Browser)
Manual Verification
Log in as an Engineer.
Open a Work Order and click "Start Work".
Verify that the "Execute SOP Checklist" button appears.
Click the button and verify the correct SOP opens for that asset type.
Tick multiple steps and click "Submit Execution".
Switch to an Admin account and verify the execution record appears in the database/logs.